node.text:
⚠️💔🇵🇸A look at what’s happening in #Palestine in the last week. Over 200 people in #Gaza dead.. including over 60 children and counting. Over 1400 injuries. 38,000 people misplaced without a home. 

Just a small taste of Palestinian life under the Israeli occupation. This has been going on for 75 years. One Palestinian child has died every 3 days in the last 20 years. Every day Palestinians go through military checkpoints, are harassed by the army and the illegal settlers- who steal their houses, burn their land, and attack Palestinians under protection of armed soldiers. 

This all began when illegal settlers attempted once again to steal the he houses from the residents of Sheikh Jarrah.. who have lived on their land for multiple generations. Protests sprung around the world and on the holiest nights of the year, in the third holiest mosque, the Israeli army stormed and attacked worshippers while they were praying. Rubber bullets, tear gas, stun grenades, you name it:

Since then people all around Palestine have been shot dead at checkpoints, at protests, and along the streets of Palestine.. all while Gaza is being bombed endlessly and the residents of Sheikh Jarrah are doing everything they can to not have their homes stolen from them. 

The world is finally waking up to see the absolute oppression and disgusting nature of the Israeli occupation of Palestine.

#FreePalestine
#GazaUnderAttack
#SaveSheikhJarrah

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by FaZe Apex on May 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'EST FANK PALESTINE'.

node.text:
🇵🇸🇵🇸❤️❤️ (Swipe) This is 10 year old me.. and next to me is a 10 year old boy from Gaza, Palestine who was my roommate and bunk buddy for 6 months. He came from across the world to a foreign country- not knowing the language- to come live with strangers (me and my family) with the hope to walk properly again after being shot in both legs when he was 9 years old. We were the same age and I had an easy life with no worries, no fear, living the best life I could pray for. And then my parents decided to house this kid. 

I remember hearing his story as a kid that he and his other 9-10 year old friends were walking to school when a soldier opened fire at the group killing one of his best friends and shooting him in both his legs. To me- this story was unfathomable and the experience was life changing.. to him and every other Palestinian living the daily struggle of occupation, it’s nothing special. 

This week 180+ people died in Gaza including 52+ children and over 1200 injuries.

There has been an average of one Palestinian child killed every three days by the occupying army over the last 20 years. Gaza is currently still under blockade and deprived of basic necessities and trapped in essentially an open air prison they can’t get out of. And nobody can get in to help. (Other than limited resources from the United Nations)

These are messages on the third slide are from him earlier this week. He messaged me this morning, so at this point I do know he’s still alive but not sure how many more of his family members and friends are not. #FreePalestine 🇵🇸❤️ #GazaUnderAttack 

‎اللهم جعلهم و اهلهم من الشهداء

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by FaZe Apex on May 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and monument.

node.text:
🇵🇸🇵🇸❤️❤️ FREE PALESTINE. Al-Aqsa is under attack. Sheikh Jarrah is under attack. This first picture of is of me at the Al-Aqsa compound. An important site for all 3 major religions that people from all around the world yearn to visit. It is currently being attacked on the absolute most important and holy nights of the year for Muslims. Swipe to see as Muslim Palestinian worshippers this week were shot with rubber bullets, beat, arrested, stun grenaded, tear gassed, & abused for worshipping inside mosque. A calculated attack on the most important nights of the year.  Nights of worship and prayer turned into nights of violence, fear, and loss of life

There has been an average of one Palestinian child killed every three days by the occupying army over the last 20 years. Yesterday 9 more children were killed. Swipe to see one of them who seemed to have loved gaming as the rest of us, pictured wearing a PUBG shirt, now another dead innocent child

The issue goes over 75 years back to our Palestinian grand parents & great grandparents who used to live peacefully on their land. Today, those same people are being forced out of the houses their great-great-grandparents built with their own hands ON TOP of the land they inherited from generations before. Swipe to see videos from this week of ILLEGAL settlers raiding the village of Sheikh Jarrah and forcing them out of their houses with the help of their army. (And their massive guns) They STEAL their houses and claim them as their own. Which are UNARGUABLY human rights violations and undisputedly international crime under United Nations law. Can you imagine someone coming into your house, kicking you out with the ARMED police’s help? The house your parents worked their entire lives to pay for? Again- a normal occurrence in the life of a Palestinian. Take a look at Jacob on the next slide explaining that its okay because if HE doesnt steal their house, somebody else will

None of these things are surprising and the Palestinian people have lived this reality and worse for their entire lives. 

Click the link in my bio... educate yourselves and others, do your part, & inshallah one day we’ll have a free Palestine ❤️🇵🇸
